1
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:26,867
[♪♪♪]

2
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:29,098
RICO:
I always get the shakes
before a drop.

3
00:00:30,263 --> 00:00:31,333
[WHIRRING]

4
00:00:31,498 --> 00:00:32,602
I had the injections.

5
00:00:35,101 --> 00:00:36,239
Hypnotic prep.

6
00:00:38,304 --> 00:00:41,046
The Federation shrink scanned
my brainwaves.

7
00:00:41,241 --> 00:00:42,686
[HISSING]

8
00:00:46,946 --> 00:00:49,358
Everything checked out.

9
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:52,862
Doc says it wasn't fear.

10
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:56,793
I could've told him that.

11
00:00:59,259 --> 00:01:02,570
A horse locked
in the starting gate isn't afraid.

12
00:01:02,762 --> 00:01:05,368
He's just ready to run.

13
00:01:19,479 --> 00:01:21,481
[♪♪♪]

14
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:45,175
DAUGHERTY:
A-Team.

15
00:01:45,338 --> 00:01:48,615
Our mission is to seize and control
the B-Dock area,

16
00:01:48,808 --> 00:01:51,846
clear away the bugs,
and evac the survivors.

17
00:01:52,011 --> 00:01:54,890
Now, once we land, we join forces
with the K-12 team

18
00:01:55,048 --> 00:01:58,518
at the fort. It's a standard
grab and go. After the rescue,

19
00:01:59,085 --> 00:02:00,689
we return to the ship, take off,

20
00:02:00,854 --> 00:02:03,095
then we blow the fort
and the bugs.

21
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:06,703
Are we clear?
ALL: Loud and clear, sir!

22
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:08,862
[♪♪♪]

23
00:02:19,572 --> 00:02:21,984
DAUGHERTY:
Go, go, go!

24
00:02:28,248 --> 00:02:29,283
[BUGS SCREECHING]

25
00:02:47,133 --> 00:02:49,135
[GUNFIRE]

26
00:02:59,746 --> 00:03:00,781
DAUGHERTY:
Report.

27
00:03:00,947 --> 00:03:03,325
GUNFODDER: Pretty bad.
Some of our men are in the far corridor.

28
00:03:03,483 --> 00:03:04,962
DAUGHERTY:
Let's get them out of there.

29
00:03:05,118 --> 00:03:08,656
Mech, we're done here. Prep to blow.
MECH: Sir.

30
00:03:08,821 --> 00:03:13,668
Holyman and Chow, on the cover.
Biggers and Crysoch hold position.

31
00:03:13,826 --> 00:03:19,003
The rest of you, follow me.
We're on a rescue mission, people!

32
00:03:28,107 --> 00:03:30,018
JONAH [OVER RADIO]:
Lieutenant Daugherty.
What is your status?

33
00:03:30,176 --> 00:03:33,157
DAUGHERTY:
Too many bugs.
No way to take back Fort Casey.

34
00:03:33,313 --> 00:03:36,419
Will hold till the John A. Warden
evacuates.

35
00:03:36,950 --> 00:03:39,624
Alesia will stand by for immediate evac.
Keep me posted.

36
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:41,992
DAUGHERTY:
Roger that. Mech!
What's your ETR?

37
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:44,362
MECH:
Almost there, sir.

38
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:46,730
[BEEPING]

39
00:03:48,828 --> 00:03:51,206
Done. Let's go.

40
00:03:52,031 --> 00:03:54,033
[BUGS SCREECHING]

41
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,072
[GRUNTING]

42
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,483
DAUGHERTY:
Charleston's down!

43
00:04:04,644 --> 00:04:06,715
Medic!
SHOCK JOCK: I'm on it.

44
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:16,698
CARL:
Have you completed
loading the crates?

45
00:04:16,856 --> 00:04:19,735
No. That is your priority.

46
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:28,004
[♪♪♪]

47
00:04:28,167 --> 00:04:29,202
Hm.

48
00:04:29,369 --> 00:04:31,542
What the hell is this about, Carl?

49
00:04:31,704 --> 00:04:33,377
Wonderful to see you again,
Carmen.

50
00:04:33,539 --> 00:04:36,782
You commandeered my damn ship.
Borrowing it. I'll give it back.

51
00:04:36,976 --> 00:04:39,684
You're never gonna take
the John A. Warden from me.

52
00:04:39,846 --> 00:04:42,850
Guards, I believe Captain Ibanez
needs an escort to the Alesia.

53
00:04:43,016 --> 00:04:44,086
[GRUNTS]

54
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,560
What do you want
with my ship, Carl?

55
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:51,064
Tsk, tsk, tsk. Carmen, that's
classified. But I can tell you this.

56
00:04:51,224 --> 00:04:54,728
This mission--
Oh, this mission will turn the tide.

57
00:04:54,894 --> 00:04:57,397
You always were
such an asshole.

58
00:04:57,563 --> 00:04:59,975
And I was always so fond of you
as well, Carmen.

59
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,612
See you on Terra.

60
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,907
Friends always, right?

61
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:15,782
[SCREECHING]

62
00:05:19,752 --> 00:05:22,232
DAUGHERTY:
A-Team, reload.

63
00:05:24,624 --> 00:05:27,468
This is A-Team leader
to Fort Casey. Evacs, come in.

64
00:05:27,627 --> 00:05:29,106
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
About goddamn time.

65
00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:31,799
It's a little crowded out here.
Exit now. Dock B.

66
00:05:31,964 --> 00:05:32,999
On our way.

67
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:36,477
Show some hustle. It's quiet now,
but that ain't gonna last.

68
00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:40,083
Evacs coming out. Keep your
eyes open and your heads down!

69
00:05:40,239 --> 00:05:42,344
I don't wanna lose
anyone to friendly fire!

70
00:05:45,578 --> 00:05:47,421
[GRUNTING]

71
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:49,516
Who's in charge?

72
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:50,820
Acting commander, sir.

73
00:05:50,983 --> 00:05:53,361
Major Henry Varro
has been relieved of duty.

74
00:05:53,553 --> 00:05:55,760
Relieved?
What the hell happened?

75
00:05:55,922 --> 00:05:59,460
This was a suicide
mission from the get-go,
fucking head case.

76
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:02,435
BUGSPRAY:
Shut your mouth, Ratzass.
You wanna be busted like Hero?

77
00:06:02,628 --> 00:06:04,630
[♪♪♪]

78
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:16,647
[GRUNTS]

79
00:06:16,843 --> 00:06:18,584
[♪♪♪]

80
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:49,413
DAUGHERTY:
We're out of here!
Let's get back to the ship.

81
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:51,850
Mech! How's it coming
with that charge?

82
00:06:52,011 --> 00:06:54,992
MECH:
Armed and dangerous.

83
00:06:58,518 --> 00:07:00,520
[ENGINE BLASTS]

84
00:07:02,822 --> 00:07:04,995
DAUGHERTY:
You have to be kidding me.

85
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:06,501
[♪♪♪]

86
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:16,646
Thanks for waiting, jackass!

87
00:07:17,336 --> 00:07:20,874
Command! If there are new orders,
let me know, goddamn it!

88
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:24,578
Are we gonna escort
the John A. Warden or not?

89
00:07:24,744 --> 00:07:26,746
[BUGS SCREECHING]

90
00:07:28,581 --> 00:07:31,255
[♪♪♪]

91
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,728
MAN:
Behind us!

92
00:07:35,888 --> 00:07:37,390
BIGGERS:
Sir! This is Biggers!

93
00:07:37,557 --> 00:07:39,935
Can't hold any more! We're--
Aah!

94
00:07:40,092 --> 00:07:42,572
You bug sons of bitches! Aah!

95
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:46,074
DAUGHERTY:
Captain Jonah, This is A-Team.

96
00:07:46,232 --> 00:07:48,872
Landing ship destroyed.
Boarding directly now.

97
00:07:49,035 --> 00:07:52,107
JONAH [OVER RADIO]:
Roger that. As soon as you're aboard,
Alesia will depart.

98
00:07:53,906 --> 00:07:57,444
DAUGHERTY:
Wedge formation!
Fall back into the Alesia!

99
00:08:05,117 --> 00:08:07,119
[♪♪♪]

100
00:08:13,626 --> 00:08:15,469
[SCREAMS]

101
00:08:18,798 --> 00:08:21,711
Hold formation.
Hold formation.

102
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,747
[SCREAMS AND GRUNTS]

103
00:08:30,576 --> 00:08:33,989
My arm! My goddamn arm!

104
00:08:35,615 --> 00:08:37,492
MAN:
Medic!

105
00:08:41,954 --> 00:08:43,592
[♪♪♪]

106
00:08:43,789 --> 00:08:45,029
Four-twenty-four,

107
00:08:46,225 --> 00:08:49,104
425, 426.

108
00:08:49,595 --> 00:08:51,666
DAUGHERTY:
Return to the ship!

109
00:08:53,432 --> 00:08:54,433
[GUNSHOTS]

110
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,103
TRIG:
Four-twenty-eight, 429,

111
00:08:57,870 --> 00:09:00,214
430, 431.

112
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:03,286
DAUGHERTY [OVER RADIO]:
Trig! Move your goddamn ass.
We're taking off.

113
00:09:03,476 --> 00:09:05,478
[♪♪♪]

114
00:09:17,356 --> 00:09:18,357
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

115
00:09:18,524 --> 00:09:20,401
DAUGHERTY:
Come on!

116
00:09:22,628 --> 00:09:24,301
BUGSPRAY:
Jump!

117
00:09:25,798 --> 00:09:27,334
[♪♪♪]

118
00:09:36,175 --> 00:09:37,279
Thanks.

119
00:09:38,344 --> 00:09:39,550
Anytime.

120
00:09:39,712 --> 00:09:41,988
Score?
TRIG: Four-thirty.

121
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,749
Give or take.

122
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,327
[RUMBLING]

123
00:09:45,484 --> 00:09:47,486
[♪♪♪]

124
00:09:58,664 --> 00:10:00,666
[BUGS SCREECHING]

125
00:10:13,813 --> 00:10:15,850
CHASE:
You gonna do it or what?

126
00:10:16,048 --> 00:10:18,085
Hit it, maestro.

127
00:10:19,518 --> 00:10:20,553
Three,

128
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:23,564
two, one, boom.

129
00:10:25,358 --> 00:10:26,701
[♪♪♪]

130
00:10:26,859 --> 00:10:28,861
[ALL CHEERING]

131
00:10:31,430 --> 00:10:35,469
Oh, come on, guys.
This shit ain't over yet.

132
00:10:39,705 --> 00:10:43,448
MAN:
Ha-ha-ha. Yeah. All right.

133
00:10:51,617 --> 00:10:53,927
So, what the hell happened
to you guys down there?

134
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:57,226
We were right on top
of a motherfucking ant hill.

135
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:58,494
Varro saved our ass.

136
00:10:58,724 --> 00:11:02,900
Then that ESP prick, Jenkins,
sent us on a death run.

137
00:11:03,062 --> 00:11:04,871
Straight into
a goddamn hive.

138
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,667
But you didn't hear
that shit from me.

139
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,402
Uh, I'm sorry,
you say something?

140
00:11:09,568 --> 00:11:11,309
DAUGHERTY:
Attention!

141
00:11:16,108 --> 00:11:18,782
You can all be proud of yourselves.

142
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:21,656
We saved some lives.

143
00:11:21,814 --> 00:11:22,815
[ALL CHEERING]

144
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:24,961
And we killed some bugs.

145
00:11:25,117 --> 00:11:27,893
But we lost
some good troopers today.

146
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,525
Here's to the dead.
ALL: And to the next man to die!

147
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:33,193
Now let's get back to Terra.

148
00:11:33,392 --> 00:11:35,201
And we can put some real glasses
in these hands.

149
00:11:35,394 --> 00:11:37,601
[ALL CHEER AND LAUGH]

150
00:11:45,504 --> 00:11:47,643
Heh. Check it out.

151
00:11:47,807 --> 00:11:51,949
What's the matter? You never saw
a flanker without her armor before?

152
00:11:52,111 --> 00:11:54,853
Yeah. But they usually
look like Ratzass.

153
00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:57,187
Ratzass?
Heh. That's what they call me.

154
00:11:57,349 --> 00:11:59,659
Because you don't give
a rat's ass about anything.

155
00:11:59,819 --> 00:12:01,127
What a surprise.
Hey,

156
00:12:01,854 --> 00:12:04,892
you want me to show you
to the shower?

157
00:12:05,057 --> 00:12:07,298
I could wash your back.

158
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:11,000
You don't wanna wash my front?

159
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:16,840
Hm.

160
00:12:18,671 --> 00:12:20,014
[LAUGHS]

161
00:12:20,172 --> 00:12:23,381
Shh. Shut up.

162
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:25,811
[♪♪♪]

163
00:12:39,558 --> 00:12:41,731
OFFICER:
Captain on the bridge.

164
00:12:42,027 --> 00:12:45,099
Stand down. This is
your ship, not mine, captain.

165
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,834
Simple respect,
Captain Ibanez.

166
00:12:46,999 --> 00:12:49,775
For what happened on Planet-P
Venta Monis alone.

167
00:12:49,969 --> 00:12:51,971
If only more strikes
were executed that way.

168
00:12:52,838 --> 00:12:54,681
I had a good team.

169
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,183
What can you tell me?

170
00:12:56,675 --> 00:12:57,710
About?

171
00:12:57,877 --> 00:12:59,117
Where's my ship?

172
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:01,053
And why does Jenkins
want it so badly?

173
00:13:01,213 --> 00:13:03,853
Believe me, if I could provide you
with any information--

174
00:13:04,016 --> 00:13:06,860
This ship is in pursuit
of the John A. Warden, isn't it?

175
00:13:07,019 --> 00:13:10,193
I understand your concern
for the John A. Warden,
Captain Ibanez,

176
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:12,393
but this is the Alesia
and we command it.

177
00:13:12,591 --> 00:13:14,798
Our orders are to return to Terra.

178
00:13:14,994 --> 00:13:17,531
Then show me the data
on the John A. Warden's path.

179
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:20,472
Where's she headed?
We don't know, captain.

180
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:24,740
We lost her signal
shortly after we began pursuit.

181
00:13:27,606 --> 00:13:30,086
Please contact me when you
find the John A. Warden.

182
00:13:30,242 --> 00:13:31,277
Aye, aye, captain.

183
00:13:36,749 --> 00:13:39,889
GUNFODDER:
Hey, man.
Don't write this up, okay?

184
00:13:40,052 --> 00:13:42,555
This is a serious wound.

185
00:13:44,557 --> 00:13:45,797
Could've been a lot worse.

186
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:49,166
I can't keep something like this
off the record. I--

187
00:13:49,929 --> 00:13:52,341
I'm gonna have to take your arm.
Fine.

188
00:13:52,531 --> 00:13:55,137
But, look, at least do
what you can to make sure

189
00:13:55,301 --> 00:13:56,939
it doesn't get back to my folks.

190
00:13:57,102 --> 00:13:58,843
You can at least do that,
right, doc?

191
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:03,283
[RUMBLING]

192
00:14:04,276 --> 00:14:05,846
Let's do this.
Um,

193
00:14:06,045 --> 00:14:07,854
why don't we wait
till the shaking stops?

194
00:14:08,047 --> 00:14:11,620
The ship will be fine.
I'm not talking about the ship.

195
00:14:14,954 --> 00:14:16,956
[♪♪♪]

196
00:14:25,431 --> 00:14:27,433
[GRUNTING]

197
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:37,115
Oh.

198
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,890
[CHUCKLES
THEN GIBBERING]

199
00:14:44,783 --> 00:14:46,091
[BOTH LAUGHING]

200
00:14:48,287 --> 00:14:51,564
Hey, newb. Dance class
is down the hall.

201
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:54,967
No. It's right here.
Care to dance?

202
00:14:55,127 --> 00:14:58,904
Heh. This ring is for fighting.
Humor me.

203
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:03,511
What's your name?
Chow.

204
00:15:03,669 --> 00:15:06,411
Well, Chow,
I don't usually dance with guys,

205
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:07,982
but in your case, heh,

206
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:09,847
I'll make an exception.

207
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:13,046
Who's your money on?
Ratzass is bigger.

208
00:15:13,212 --> 00:15:15,158
Not much upstairs--
Whatever, dude.

209
00:15:15,314 --> 00:15:18,659
Ratzass gets in one good solid hit
and Chow's going down.

210
00:15:18,817 --> 00:15:20,819
Shit, if he can ever
land a punch.

211
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:22,624
Chow's fast, man.

212
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:28,065
All right, fighters,
to your corners.

213
00:15:30,896 --> 00:15:35,072
RATZASS:
You back out now,
I won't think any less of you.

214
00:15:36,168 --> 00:15:39,411
When I ring the bell,
come out fighting.

215
00:15:41,140 --> 00:15:43,746
They're gonna miss you
when you're gone.

216
00:15:43,909 --> 00:15:44,944
Hm.

217
00:15:45,144 --> 00:15:47,146
[♪♪♪]

218
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,723
[YELLS]

219
00:15:50,582 --> 00:15:52,425
Aw...

220
00:15:59,892 --> 00:16:01,565
[GRUNTING]

221
00:16:10,736 --> 00:16:12,443
Good thing
there's not much upstairs.

222
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:14,413
Don't have to worry
about brain damage.

223
00:16:14,573 --> 00:16:16,575
Hey, damage this.

224
00:16:19,044 --> 00:16:20,079
[GRUNTS]

225
00:16:30,255 --> 00:16:31,393
Hey.

226
00:16:31,557 --> 00:16:33,127
[GASPS]

227
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:39,340
[GRUNTS]

228
00:16:40,499 --> 00:16:42,501
[CHASE & MECH LAUGHING]

229
00:16:43,569 --> 00:16:45,310
CHASE:
Did you see that?

230
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:47,815
[TRIG CHUCKLES]

231
00:16:50,109 --> 00:16:52,851
Didn't know you had it in you.

232
00:16:54,213 --> 00:16:57,956
Flash of inspiration. Unh.

233
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:05,099
E057, E057.

234
00:17:05,257 --> 00:17:09,103
E057.

235
00:17:09,261 --> 00:17:11,138
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

236
00:17:12,097 --> 00:17:13,872
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

237
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:16,035
[GRUNTING]

238
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:18,371
[CHIME]

239
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:23,818
[BUZZER SOUNDS]

240
00:17:23,976 --> 00:17:25,546
[GRUNTS]

241
00:17:26,178 --> 00:17:28,681
BUGSPRAY:
Thanks, I really appreciate...

242
00:17:28,847 --> 00:17:30,292
it.

243
00:17:34,019 --> 00:17:35,054
Hm.

244
00:17:35,687 --> 00:17:37,325
[BEEPING]

245
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:39,799
They can't get me a bed
till tomorrow.

246
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,633
Thanks for letting me use
the com...?

247
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:44,240
Tia.

248
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:47,138
Tia Durer. Trig is fine.

249
00:17:47,299 --> 00:17:50,405
Otis Hacks. Bugspray.

250
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:53,707
Hey, uh...

251
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:58,078
Thanks for the catch.
At Fort Casey.

252
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:03,655
Sleeping with a gun?
You must know something
I don't.

253
00:18:04,283 --> 00:18:08,891
Morita XXX sniper rifle.
Classic.

254
00:18:12,057 --> 00:18:13,161
Hm.

255
00:18:13,692 --> 00:18:16,036
You've got a nice smile
for a psych job.

256
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:18,232
Thanks...

257
00:18:18,497 --> 00:18:20,204
I think.

258
00:18:20,699 --> 00:18:23,179
So up for a little training?

259
00:18:23,335 --> 00:18:26,942
I think I've had about all
the target practice
I can stand today.

260
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:32,522
Yeah. I was thinking about
something a little more strenuous.

261
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:40,056
You didn't really use
the intercom, did you?

262
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:43,089
Would you like to know more?
Heh.

263
00:18:44,189 --> 00:18:45,259
Oh.

264
00:18:51,396 --> 00:18:54,138
Everyone's doing their part.

265
00:19:03,942 --> 00:19:05,944
[♪♪♪]

266
00:19:06,945 --> 00:19:08,891
Major Henry Varro.

267
00:19:11,383 --> 00:19:15,627
One of the most decorated
officers in the Federation.

268
00:19:17,923 --> 00:19:22,429
You've run long-range ops
in places even God's given up on.

269
00:19:27,099 --> 00:19:29,306
What did you do?

270
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:31,510
Why won't you talk?

271
00:19:31,937 --> 00:19:33,280
And why won't your men talk?

272
00:19:53,158 --> 00:19:54,330
Heh.

273
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:56,528
[WHIRRING]

274
00:19:58,096 --> 00:19:59,473
There are modifications

275
00:19:59,631 --> 00:20:02,339
you can score on the black market
when you get to Terra.

276
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:05,038
But as far as what
the Federation will pay for,

277
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,514
it's still a good prosthetic.
Got it.

278
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:10,984
Nice job. Don't know
what you were nervous about.

279
00:20:11,143 --> 00:20:14,215
I bet this looks as good
as all the others.

280
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:18,051
What others?
You're my first.

281
00:20:18,517 --> 00:20:22,966
Matter of fact, you're the first guy
I've worked on that's actually lived.

282
00:20:27,693 --> 00:20:29,866
TRIG:
Every commander
I've ever served under

283
00:20:30,028 --> 00:20:32,668
tries to get me to use
a regulation gun.

284
00:20:32,831 --> 00:20:36,701
That is, until they see
how many I kill with that one.

285
00:20:36,935 --> 00:20:38,642
Then they don't ask me anymore.

286
00:20:38,804 --> 00:20:40,806
[♪♪♪]

287
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:45,147
My parents made that rifle.

288
00:20:48,046 --> 00:20:50,754
There was an armory
in my home town.

289
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:53,656
Everyone worked there.

290
00:20:57,856 --> 00:21:02,032
That is, until the bugs melted
the place with a plasma bomb.

291
00:21:02,461 --> 00:21:07,171
Soldiers, civilians, families.

292
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:10,077
Everyone died.

293
00:21:12,504 --> 00:21:17,249
I swore then
that I'd kill just as many bugs.

294
00:21:19,544 --> 00:21:21,524
And I'd do it with that gun.

295
00:21:22,848 --> 00:21:24,691
That's why you count?

296
00:21:26,351 --> 00:21:29,924
TRIG:
No. That's why it counts.

297
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:40,432
[♪♪♪]

298
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:02,893
[FAUCET SQUEAKS]

299
00:22:07,092 --> 00:22:09,072
[GRUNTS]

300
00:22:09,227 --> 00:22:11,571
Goddamn you, Carl.

301
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:14,966
[ALARM WAILING]

302
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:23,580
Where'd you learn that haymaker?
Dance class.

303
00:22:23,742 --> 00:22:27,588
Shit. I knew it. I just felt it.

304
00:22:27,746 --> 00:22:29,748
We aren't gonna see Terra
any time soon.

305
00:22:29,915 --> 00:22:33,158
Aw, you're a pessimist.
Specialist, actually.

306
00:22:33,318 --> 00:22:36,527
Well, almost.
Five points short
on the ESP test.

307
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:38,690
If one more jack
had been a diamond,

308
00:22:38,857 --> 00:22:41,303
I wouldn't be here
with you dumbasses.

309
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:43,437
[SCOFFS]

310
00:22:43,595 --> 00:22:45,097
You son of a bitch.

311
00:22:45,263 --> 00:22:48,267
That's how you always know
when I'm in the shower.

312
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:52,042
So can you tell
what I'm thinking now?

313
00:22:52,204 --> 00:22:54,275
MECH:
Hell, even I know
what you're thinking now.

314
00:22:54,439 --> 00:22:56,646
You make me sick.

315
00:22:59,077 --> 00:23:00,147
Hm.

316
00:23:01,146 --> 00:23:04,491
What's up, Lieutenant Daugherty?
I thought you were in Medical.

317
00:23:04,983 --> 00:23:08,328
Ah, wasn't as bad
as it looked.

318
00:23:10,555 --> 00:23:11,556
Ah.

319
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:13,066
Glad you two could make it.

320
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:15,205
MAN 1: Ow!
MAN 2: Whoo!

321
00:23:23,468 --> 00:23:24,469
[♪♪♪]

322
00:23:24,636 --> 00:23:25,979
RICO:
At ease.

323
00:23:28,039 --> 00:23:30,485
I wanted to brief you all
personally, ﬁrst and foremost

324
00:23:30,642 --> 00:23:33,179
because I know the sacriﬁces
that both the crew

325
00:23:33,345 --> 00:23:36,883
of the Alesia as well as
the defenders of Fort Casey
have made

326
00:23:37,048 --> 00:23:39,153
and the great losses
that you've suffered.

327
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:42,560
And second, I know you could
all use some R&R about now.

328
00:23:42,721 --> 00:23:44,894
Believe me, I've been there myself.

329
00:23:45,056 --> 00:23:48,162
But, unfortunately,
we have a situation.

330
00:23:48,326 --> 00:23:49,828
MAN 3: What?
Stow it.

331
00:23:49,995 --> 00:23:52,339
The John A. Warden
has gone silent.

332
00:23:52,497 --> 00:23:56,445
The Alesia is the only starship
in the area of last contact.

333
00:23:56,635 --> 00:23:58,911
I have ordered your captain
to divert course,

334
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:01,880
ﬁnd the Warden, and investigate.

335
00:24:03,175 --> 00:24:05,177
Any questions?

336
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:06,682
Yeah.

337
00:24:06,845 --> 00:24:09,758
I speak for everyone
from Fort Casey when I say this.

338
00:24:09,915 --> 00:24:10,950
Shut the fuck up.

339
00:24:11,149 --> 00:24:13,561
It's okay. Go on.

340
00:24:14,686 --> 00:24:17,223
We're only going in
if Hero takes point.

341
00:24:17,923 --> 00:24:20,426
Hero?
Major Henry Varro,

342
00:24:20,592 --> 00:24:22,868
Commander of Fort Casey,
General Rico.

343
00:24:23,028 --> 00:24:24,769
Right.

344
00:24:24,930 --> 00:24:27,308
Arrested by Dr. Carl Jenkins
for insubordination

345
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:30,242
at the battle of Fort Casey.

346
00:24:30,702 --> 00:24:34,206
Fine. If Major Varro chooses
to participate in this mission,

347
00:24:34,372 --> 00:24:36,579
the mobile infantry
will accept his service.

348
00:24:36,741 --> 00:24:38,448
However, this will not,
in any way

349
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:41,056
be prejudicial to his trial,
is that understood?

350
00:24:41,213 --> 00:24:42,419
Understood, sir.

351
00:24:42,581 --> 00:24:46,791
We'll probably lose communications
as you cross the nebula.

352
00:24:46,952 --> 00:24:51,059
Godspeed, Alesia. Dismissed.

353
00:24:51,890 --> 00:24:54,200
DAUGHERTY:
Assemble in the staging area.

354
00:24:55,126 --> 00:24:56,935
A word, Captain Ibanez.

355
00:24:57,095 --> 00:24:59,006
[DOOR CLOSES]

356
00:24:59,197 --> 00:25:01,234
Why did you let him take my ship?

357
00:25:01,399 --> 00:25:02,400
[SIGHS]

358
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:05,946
Carmen, it's not your ship.
It belongs to the Terran Federation.

359
00:25:06,104 --> 00:25:10,143
General Rico, perhaps you recall
there was a certain young trooper

360
00:25:10,308 --> 00:25:13,016
who was with me when
the Roger Young went down.

361
00:25:13,211 --> 00:25:17,660
I vowed that would never happen
to a ship under my command.

362
00:25:18,416 --> 00:25:20,020
This is not my choice.

363
00:25:20,218 --> 00:25:22,858
I mean, look, I don't care
what you thought of Carl

364
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:25,865
back when we knew him
and I don't care what you think now.

365
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:29,267
He's minister of Paranormal Warfare
and high command has authorized

366
00:25:29,427 --> 00:25:31,737
him to use the John A. Warden.

367
00:25:32,264 --> 00:25:36,269
Look, Carmen, this is a mission
that's so classiﬁed,

368
00:25:36,434 --> 00:25:38,937
I don't even know what--
Look how well it's going.

369
00:25:39,237 --> 00:25:42,343
You know the John A. Warden
like the back of your hand.

370
00:25:42,507 --> 00:25:44,953
I need you to go aboard
with the insertion team.

371
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:47,249
I looked at the manifest.

372
00:25:47,445 --> 00:25:50,790
That ship didn't just go dark.

373
00:25:50,949 --> 00:25:53,293
Her signal was turned off.

374
00:25:53,451 --> 00:25:55,522
And you know as well as I do,
the only one

375
00:25:55,687 --> 00:26:00,397
who has the gall to run a Federation
starship dark is Carl Jenkins.

376
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:03,472
And how do you know
we're even close to my ship?

377
00:26:03,628 --> 00:26:07,371
Before we lost contact,
we analyzed some of
the scattered signals.

378
00:26:07,532 --> 00:26:09,409
Calculating course and speed,

379
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:12,071
we were able to get
a good estimate of its location.

380
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:15,149
Now, it's not spot on,
but we can get you
pretty damn close.

381
00:26:15,307 --> 00:26:17,309
[♪♪♪]

382
00:26:18,643 --> 00:26:24,821
Fine. I'll do it.
But not to save Carl's sorry ass.

383
00:26:24,983 --> 00:26:27,020
I'll do it to take back my ship.

384
00:26:28,486 --> 00:26:31,365
You just be careful.
We need you back intact

385
00:26:31,523 --> 00:26:33,696
when this thing is over.

386
00:26:35,393 --> 00:26:37,395
Thank you, Johnny.

387
00:26:37,929 --> 00:26:40,102
Hey, Carmen,
when this thing is over,

388
00:26:40,298 --> 00:26:44,440
maybe you and I can
meet at Zim's and, uh... Uh...

389
00:26:44,603 --> 00:26:49,440
Yeah. Yeah. Sheesh.

390
00:26:49,674 --> 00:26:51,517
I gotta tell you.

391
00:26:51,676 --> 00:26:55,419
This will in no way
be prejudicial to your trial.

392
00:26:57,215 --> 00:27:00,958
Aw, come on. I didn't have
anything to do with any of this.

393
00:27:01,119 --> 00:27:03,690
I'm just the damn janitor
trying to clean it up.

394
00:27:03,855 --> 00:27:05,334
[DOOR OPENS]

395
00:27:07,626 --> 00:27:10,232
Look, major,
I'm no more enthusiastic

396
00:27:10,395 --> 00:27:13,706
about saving Carl Jenkins
than you are.

397
00:27:14,232 --> 00:27:16,735
But your men want you.

398
00:27:17,736 --> 00:27:21,343
And something tells me
we're gonna need you.

399
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,275
Hm.

400
00:27:23,441 --> 00:27:27,218
MAN [OVER INTERCOM]:
Lieutenant Daugherty,
we've found the John A. Warden.

401
00:27:27,379 --> 00:27:31,156
Tell Captain Jonah to move
to standoff range. I'll be right up.

402
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,896
So which is it?

403
00:27:43,762 --> 00:27:46,368
Get these chains off me.

404
00:27:47,866 --> 00:27:49,868
[♪♪♪]

405
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:55,140
[♪♪♪]

406
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:12,666
It'd be too bad
if a stray shot hit Jenkins.

407
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:15,804
I know you're pissed
but don't think shit like that.

408
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:19,430
They threw Hero into the brig.
You or me, Holyman or Kharon,

409
00:28:19,597 --> 00:28:21,838
what do you think they'd do
to grunts like us?

410
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:24,037
They'd shove us
out of a goddamn airlock.

411
00:28:24,202 --> 00:28:26,773
So I gotta watch my ass?
Yeah.

412
00:28:26,938 --> 00:28:30,317
But if you're not gonna do that,
at least watch mine.

413
00:28:38,116 --> 00:28:41,654
Oh. Oh, man, fuck you.

414
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:45,693
Can't believe I'm the only one
not getting laid around here.

415
00:28:47,425 --> 00:28:48,802
[ICE BLONDE CHUCKLES]

416
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:50,803
Looks like you've got
your bases covered.

417
00:28:51,362 --> 00:28:54,468
Tell me, Holyman,
which one's gonna save you today?

418
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,578
[CHUCKLES]

419
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:06,154
I can take care of myself.

420
00:29:12,150 --> 00:29:15,893
Women, they make
the highs higher and
the lows more frequent.

421
00:29:16,054 --> 00:29:18,694
Are atheists
the only philosophers
you can quote?

422
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:25,004
I find that believers
such as you say so few things
worth writing down.

423
00:29:25,163 --> 00:29:30,169
And I've found that he who looks
so forward to the abyss

424
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:32,178
is simply afraid of the light.

425
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:34,043
Hm.

426
00:29:34,205 --> 00:29:35,741
I'm gonna go get you a pen.

427
00:29:35,907 --> 00:29:38,444
Wait, did you just make that up?

428
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:40,920
No, no, I'm not writing that down.

429
00:29:41,579 --> 00:29:43,581
[♪♪♪]

430
00:29:45,183 --> 00:29:49,859
John A. Warden, this is the Alesia,
please respond.

431
00:29:50,522 --> 00:29:51,933
I've tried everything.

432
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:55,936
Voice, radio flash,
even light code. Nothing.

433
00:29:56,094 --> 00:29:59,940
Keep trying, lieutenant.
IBANEZ: Zoom in on the bridge.

434
00:30:01,266 --> 00:30:03,712
JONAH:
Maybe they can't hear us.

435
00:30:03,868 --> 00:30:07,372
They'd have to know
what our objective is.

436
00:30:07,539 --> 00:30:10,884
Bridge, this is your captain.
Respond now.

437
00:30:11,042 --> 00:30:14,319
If you do not respond, we will board.

438
00:30:21,452 --> 00:30:25,298
Board it.
That's not my ship anymore.

439
00:30:27,592 --> 00:30:29,594
[♪♪♪]

440
00:30:54,786 --> 00:30:56,595
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

441
00:30:56,754 --> 00:30:58,165
RATZASS:
Kids?

442
00:31:00,758 --> 00:31:02,499
Husband?

443
00:31:03,561 --> 00:31:06,667
Died on Planet 4976.

444
00:31:06,831 --> 00:31:12,042
Hey, the way I figure it,
the bug's got more reason
to be scared than I do.

445
00:31:12,203 --> 00:31:16,583
I've killed hundreds of them,
they killed zero of me.

446
00:31:17,275 --> 00:31:18,447
Uh--

447
00:31:18,610 --> 00:31:20,214
[RATZASS SIGHS]

448
00:31:20,378 --> 00:31:22,483
Oh, man.

449
00:31:24,382 --> 00:31:25,861
TRIG:
Listen.

450
00:31:26,818 --> 00:31:29,697
I want you to do me a favor.
Yeah?

451
00:31:29,854 --> 00:31:34,394
If I don't make it, I don't care
what happens to my body.

452
00:31:34,592 --> 00:31:37,801
But try to get my rifle scope,
will you?

453
00:31:37,962 --> 00:31:40,636
And have it buried
in my home town.

454
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:48,116
Look, I don't like funerals.
Do me a favor. Don't get killed.

455
00:31:48,606 --> 00:31:49,744
Heh.

456
00:31:55,013 --> 00:31:57,015
[♪♪♪]

457
00:32:19,170 --> 00:32:21,446
Okay, boys and girls.

458
00:32:22,573 --> 00:32:24,883
Looks like this is gonna be
my last mission.

459
00:32:25,043 --> 00:32:26,920
So let's make it a good one.

460
00:32:27,645 --> 00:32:30,421
Our job is to retake
the John A. Warden,

461
00:32:30,581 --> 00:32:32,185
rescue any and all survivors

462
00:32:32,350 --> 00:32:35,559
and exterminate any resistance
we might find.

463
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,222
You got that?

464
00:32:37,388 --> 00:32:38,958
ALL:
Sir, yes, sir!

465
00:32:40,692 --> 00:32:44,663
All right, troopers,
let's get the lady her ship back.

466
00:32:45,229 --> 00:32:47,231
ALL:
Hoo-ah!

467
00:32:54,973 --> 00:32:57,044
JONAH [OVER RADIO]:
Initiate docking procedure.

468
00:32:57,208 --> 00:32:59,688
MAN:
Initiating docking procedure.

469
00:33:02,914 --> 00:33:06,259
Team one:
Lieutenant Daugherty,
Ice, Trig, Mech,

470
00:33:06,417 --> 00:33:09,830
Shock Jock leading
Captain Ibanez to the bridge.

471
00:33:10,621 --> 00:33:15,161
Team two: Chase, Kharon, Chow,
Bugspray, Gunfodder, Ratzass,

472
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:18,830
Holyman, and the rest, you're
coming with me to the engine room.

473
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:22,604
Don't know what we're gonna find
in there so be ready for anything.

474
00:33:22,767 --> 00:33:24,007
Let's go.

475
00:33:26,437 --> 00:33:28,439
[♪♪♪]

476
00:33:33,478 --> 00:33:37,984
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
Gravity zero, oxygen level yellow,
ready to board the John A. Warden.

477
00:34:05,176 --> 00:34:06,280
DAUGHERTY:
We're in.

478
00:34:06,444 --> 00:34:08,685
Team one moving toward the bridge.

479
00:34:16,821 --> 00:34:20,268
HERO:
Team two boarding.
Moving toward the engine room.

480
00:34:23,561 --> 00:34:25,336
[♪♪♪]

481
00:34:45,817 --> 00:34:47,797
DAUGHERTY:
Something up ahead.

482
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:50,995
No...

483
00:34:54,392 --> 00:34:56,702
Oh, my God.

484
00:34:59,197 --> 00:35:02,371
DAUGHERTY:
Team two, we've got
bodies near the bridge.

485
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,877
HERO:
We've got bodies everywhere.

486
00:35:09,607 --> 00:35:11,348
CHASE:
Ugh. Man, they've been bug-ripped.

487
00:35:11,909 --> 00:35:15,015
HERO:
Infestation confirmed.
Stay sharp, people.

488
00:35:15,179 --> 00:35:17,125
DAUGHERTY [OVER RADIO]:
Nearing objective.

489
00:35:19,517 --> 00:35:22,521
Daugherty to team two,
we're on the bridge.

490
00:35:25,056 --> 00:35:27,127
And it ain't pretty.

491
00:35:35,633 --> 00:35:38,239
Got multiple casualties...

492
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:42,644
and one dead bug.

493
00:35:45,943 --> 00:35:47,752
All clear.

494
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:50,489
Shock Jock.

495
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:57,263
SHOCK JOCK:
Massive tearing wounds.

496
00:35:57,421 --> 00:35:58,661
[SHOCK JOCK RETCHES]

497
00:35:58,856 --> 00:36:00,460
Oh, my God.

498
00:36:05,229 --> 00:36:07,072
My crew.

499
00:36:12,303 --> 00:36:16,274
