706
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:21,531
Damn it.

707
00:53:21,698 --> 00:53:23,336
[BUGS SCREECHING]

708
00:53:26,469 --> 00:53:27,846
Fire!

709
00:53:28,038 --> 00:53:29,847
[ALL YELLING]

710
00:54:34,004 --> 00:54:35,176
WOMAN:
General.

711
00:54:35,338 --> 00:54:38,876
A Federation starship has just
emerged from the Marjizon Wormhole.

712
00:54:39,042 --> 00:54:42,455
It's... It's the John A. Warden.

713
00:54:42,612 --> 00:54:44,785
On screen.
They're receiving our signal, sir.

714
00:54:44,981 --> 00:54:48,622
Any response?
No, sir, they're not responding.

715
00:54:49,619 --> 00:54:51,758
Something's wrong.

716
00:54:51,921 --> 00:54:54,800
Why would they head back
towards Earth?

717
00:54:54,991 --> 00:54:58,200
Sir, if they keep their current
trajectory, the John A. Warden...

718
00:54:58,695 --> 00:55:01,369
Sir, it's heading straight for us.

719
00:55:02,766 --> 00:55:06,304
John A. Warden.
This is General Rico. Come in.

720
00:55:06,936 --> 00:55:09,815
John A. Warden,
this is the L-6 Base.

721
00:55:10,006 --> 00:55:12,145
If you do not change course
immediately,

722
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:14,915
we will be forced to engage.

723
00:55:15,078 --> 00:55:18,457
Repeat, the L-6 Base
will take defensive action

724
00:55:18,615 --> 00:55:21,425
if you do not change course.

725
00:55:21,718 --> 00:55:24,597
John A. Warden, respond.

726
00:55:28,825 --> 00:55:31,135
Talk to me, Carmen.

